C2=A0also=C2=A0Lord Rama is his=C2=A0p=\r\nast life. Similarly,=C2=A0these souls (Ramakrishna and \nMa=C2=A0Sarada and =\r\ntheir disciples)=C2=A0are of such high caliber that they do come back \nwhen=\r\n it is designed and needed for them to come back and perform some strong \no=\r\nbjectives and set in motion a spiritual impulse in this land based on the \n=\r\nnecessities of the specific desh-kaal-patra. Therefore what they do will be=\r\n \nbased purely on the zeitgeist - spirit of the times - when they incarnate=\r\n.=C2=A0 For \nall one knows, Ramakrishna may not incarnate as a simple rusti=\r\nc villager any \nmore, but rather=C2=A0as a well-educated,=C2=A0city-bred in=\r\ndividual with the practical \nintelligence of ten Chanakyas who might end up=\r\n changing the political and \nspiritual future of this land for centuries to=\r\n come, which is what the necessity \nof the present=C2=A0times really are. \n=\r\n\n=C2=A0\nWe already have an overdose of Swamis and Babas and Mas and Bhagwan=\r\ns and their \nashrams and their teeming millions as followers. What we need =\r\nis someone who=C2=A0may \nor may not have an ashram, who may or may not pose=\r\n as a Guru in the traditional \nsense, who may or may not be a glib talker (=\r\nas so many of the Babas and Mas are \nthese days), but who has the necessary=\r\n might and power to affect or initiate \nchanges in this land which would be=\r\n of an irrevocable nature.=C2=A0 It is time for a \n1000 years of history to=\r\n change. And only a soul of Ramakrishna or Ma Sarada&#39;s \ncaliber can do it. =\r\nAnyone lesser, would only fizz out=C2=A0with time.\n=C2=A0\nNot that=C2=A0the=\r\ny (Ramakrishna or Ma Sarada or=C2=A0Swamiji) will find the work to be \neasy=\r\n at all. For startes, the dunces would be in confederacy against them. When=\r\n \nVivekanada, before he became world famous, had gone to Kasi, he was bitte=\r\nrly \nopposed by the &#39;scholarly&#39; pandits of the city on various issues. Then=\r\n a young \nnot-yet-famous Vivekananda got angry and decided he will leave Ka=\r\nsi and never \nreturn to that city untill he &quot;falls on society like a thunde=\r\nrbolt&quot;. Well, that \nis precisely what he did. He fell on Indian society lik=\r\ne a thunderbolt, after \nwhich those very pandits of Kasi wrote to him, aski=\r\nng him to come and grace \ntheir city! \n\n=C2=A0\nSo let us keep our fingers c=\r\nrossed and not=C2=A0focus on emtpy speculations, rather \nwait for the most =\r\ninteresting coming=C2=A0decade to unfold in all its=C2=A0sound and fury.\n=\r\n=C2=A0\n-Regards\n=C2=A0Rajarshi\n=C2=A0\n\n=C2=A0 \nNamaste Ranjan,\n\n&gt; After you=\r\n die, what would be your name and religion and nationality\n\nName can change=\r\n on rebirth. Though religion usually stays the same, it CAN \nchange. Nation=\r\nality can of course change too. Job, skills, external nature, \nlooks, gende=\r\nr, even yoni (human, cow, goat, chicken, tiger etc) can all change \nfrom bi=\r\nrth to birth.\n\nBasically, the seed of one&#39;s new birth is formed at the time=\r\n of one&#39;s death. As \none&#39;s connection is severed with the body, the last de=\r\nsires/thoughts/ponderings \nof the mind become the seed for the next life. N=\r\nature chooses for one a future \ncourse that allows one to pursue those desi=\r\nres, as much as allowed by one&#39;s \nprevious karmas and debts.\n\nIf one is abl=\r\ne to not entertain ANY desire as one element after another \nevaporates in o=\r\nne&#39;s existence, one becomes liberated. All the spiritual sadhana \nwe do is =\r\na dress rehearsal.\n\n* * *\n\n&gt; when we see you again and do you know how we\n&gt;=\r\n shall recognize you, IF WE EVER MEET YOU?\n\nIf I and you like each other an=\r\nd your rebirth and my rebirth meet each other, \nthey will start off taking =\r\na liking to each other. If I and you dislike each \nother and your rebirth a=\r\nnd my rebirth meet each other, they will start off \ndisliking each other. T=\r\nhis will happen without either being consciously aware of \nwho one was and =\r\nwho the other person was, in the last life.\n\nInstead, if your question is h=\r\now we can recognize that so and so person is a \nrebirth of Swami Vivekanand=\r\na, so and so person is a rebirth of Paramahamsa \nYogananda etc, the answer =\r\nis complex.\n\nThe reborn person may not look like the old person or do simil=\r\nar work or have \nmuch *external* similarity. So it is difficult to &quot;recogni=\r\nze&quot; one. After all, \nRama advocated eka patni vrata (one wife principle), w=\r\nhile Krishna had thousands \nof wives. Rama was a great warrior and killed R=\r\navana in the biggest war of his \ntimes. Krishna was a key player in the big=\r\ngest war of his time, but did not take \na weapon at all. The game can be di=\r\nffent in each coming..\n\n* * *\n\nWhen it comes to recognizing the rebirth of =\r\na great soul, it can become a trap.\n\nRamakrishna explicitly told Sarada Mat=\r\na that he would be back after 100 years \nand that everybody else who came w=\r\nith him would have to come back with him. When \nSarada Mata and Lakshmi Dev=\r\ni protested, he said they did not have a choice! Even \nSwami Vivekananda sa=\r\nid once in USA, &quot;I have to come back once more. The Master \nsaid I am to co=\r\nme back once more with him&quot;. When questioned &quot;you have to come \nback becaus=\r\ne Shri Ramakrishna says so&quot;, he replied, &quot;souls like that have great \npower=\r\n, Madam&quot;. On another occasion, Ramakrishna said that people would get \nlibe=\r\nrated en masse during his next coming and that would be the last opportunit=\r\ny \nfor a long time to come.\n\nInterestingly, two good saints claimed to be r=\r\ne-incarnations of Ramakrishna \nsince then. One of them is wrong (or perhaps=\r\n both!). Another good saint \nsuggested that she is the re-incarnation of Sa=\r\nrada Mata. Satya Sai Baba said \nthat he identified a particular young man a=\r\ns the reincarnation of Swami \nVivekananda. Ramakrishna was surrounded by Sa=\r\nrada Mata and more than twenty \ndisciples of a very high caliber and differ=\r\nent aptitudes. Together, they nearly \nmoulded the direction of spiritual In=\r\ndia for the next century. None of the \nclaimants of rebirthhood are surroun=\r\nded by people of such caliber or fit the \nbill.\n\nThus, there can be false c=\r\nlaimants to the rebirthhood of a great soul! It is not \nthat they are lying=\r\n. They may simply be deluding themselves and of course ego is \nthe root of =\r\ndelusion!\n\nIn fact, is it necessary to recognize whether X is a rebirth of =\r\nY, given that X \nand Y are different and play a different game? A small dis=\r\ncussion on this point \nvis-a-vis Ramakrishna Paramahamsa&#39;s example can be f=\r\nound in:\n\nhttp://groups.yahoo.com/group/vedic-wisdom/message/807\n\n* * *\n\nTh=\r\nough external factors like nationality, religion, name, job, looks, gender =\r\netc \ncan change, some internal factors may remain the same. Moreover, who o=\r\nne likes, \nwho one dislikes, what values one is attracted to internally, et=\r\nc, may remain \nessentially the same.\n\nFor example, suppose rajput king Prit=\r\nhviraj was reborn as Muslim emperor Akbar \n(as said by Vimalananda). One wa=\r\ns a Hindu and the other was a Muslim. However, \nboth were very brave, unafr=\r\naid of death, inherently spiritual, had a refined \ntaste in fine arts and h=\r\nad deep conviction. The previous connections with \nrajputs resulted in Akba=\r\nr being born and raised when his mother was hiding at a \nrajput household, =\r\nbefore moving to Delhi. Despite being a Muslim, he actually \nhelped the Hin=\r\ndu causes (to the extent possible at that time) by putting an end \nto barba=\r\nric practices like killing defeated Hindu kings and all Hindu priests in \nc=\r\nonquered places. He promoted acceptance of other faiths, canceled pilgrimag=\r\ne \ntaxes on Hindus and even came up with his own religion of humanity towar=\r\nds the \nend of his life by integrating various religions. In one life, he t=\r\nried to save \nIndia from invading barbarians. In another, he was born as a =\r\ncultured man amid \nbarbarians and tried to save India by changing the ways =\r\nof his own people. There \nis a subtle continuity in the agenda at a deeper =\r\nlevel!\n\nBest regards,\nNarasimha\n-------------------------------------------=\r\n---------------\nFree Jyotish Software, Free Jyotish Lessons, Jyotish Writin=\r\ngs,\n&quot;Do It Yourself&quot; ritual manuals for short Homam and Pitri Tarpana:\nhttp=\r\n://www.VedicAstrologer.org\nFilms that make a difference: http://SaraswatiFi=\r\nlms.org\nSpirituality: http://groups.yahoo.com/group/vedic-wisdom\nJyotish wr=\r\nitings: http://groups.yahoo.com/group/JyotishWritings\n---------------------=\r\n-------------------------------------\n\n--- In JyotishGroup@yahoogroups.com,=\r\n &quot;rohinicrystal&quot; &lt;jyotish_vani@...&gt; wrote:\n&gt;\n&gt; Dear Lokesh_ji,\n&gt; \n&gt; As near=\r\nly ALL of do except this &quot;BABAJI&quot; Character described in Lahiri Mahashay \n&gt;=\r\n(no connection with the ayanamshaa that is causing lot of problems for many=\r\n!), \n&gt;Yukteshwar and Yognanda and Kriya Yoga -- shall probably die and hope=\r\nfully be \n&gt;born again -- here is a simple question from a simpleton:\n&gt; \n&gt; A=\r\nfter you die, what would be your name and religion and nationality, when we=\r\n \n&gt;see you again and do you know how we shall recognize you, IF WE EVER MEE=\r\nT YOU?\n&gt; \n&gt; I am not being FLIPPANT at all but just reminding you and mysel=\r\nf how evanescent \n&gt;each of us truly ARE!\n&gt; \n&gt; Rohiniranjan\n\n\n\n_____________=\r\n___________________\nFrom: Narasimha PVR Rao &lt;pvr@...&gt;\nTo: vedic-ast=\r\nrology@yahoogroups.com; JyotishGroup@yahoogroups.com; \nvedic-wisdom@yahoogr=\r\noups.com\nSent: Tue, 27 July, 2010 3:22:21 AM\nSubject: [vedic-wisdom] On Reb=\r\nirth (Re: Ra