a etc etc) when they had&nbsp;incarnated. &lt;/P&gt;\n&lt;P&gt;&nb=\r\nsp;&lt;/P&gt;\n&lt;P&gt;So unless this condition is met, (which Ramakrishna himself had =\r\nspecified in his last birth), most of the Ramakrishna or Ma Sarada reincarn=\r\nation-claimants have to be dis-qualified. &lt;/P&gt;\n&lt;P&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/P&gt;\n&lt;P&gt;Some people=\r\n have an impression that if and when Ramakrishna and Ma Sarada and Swamiji =\r\nreincarnate, they would have an association with the Ramakrishna Mission. T=\r\nhis is, in my opinion, an incorrect assumption. When Lord Krishna was born,=\r\n he did not spend his time trying to find out where is Ayodhya since he was=\r\n&nbsp;also&nbsp;Lord Rama is his&nbsp;past life. Similarly,&nbsp;these soul=\r\ns (Ramakrishna and Ma&nbsp;Sarada and their disciples)&nbsp;are of such hig=\r\nh caliber that they do come back when it is designed and needed for them to=\r\n come back and perform some strong objectives and set in motion a spiritual=\r\n impulse in this land based on the necessities of the specific desh-kaal-pa=\r\ntra. Therefore what they do will be based purely on the zeitgeist - spirit =\r\nof the times - when they incarnate.&nbsp; For all one knows, Ramakrishna ma=\r\ny not incarnate as a simple rustic villager any more, but rather&nbsp;as a =\r\nwell-educated,&nbsp;city-bred individual with the\n practical intelligence o=\r\nf ten Chanakyas who might end up changing the political and spiritual futur=\r\ne of this land for centuries to come, which is what the necessity of the pr=\r\nesent&nbsp;times really are. &lt;/P&gt;\n&lt;P&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/P&gt;\n&lt;P&gt;We already have an overd=\r\nose of Swamis and Babas and Mas and Bhagwans and their ashrams and their te=\r\neming millions as followers. What we need is someone who&nbsp;may or may no=\r\nt have an ashram, who may or may not pose as a Guru in the traditional sens=\r\ne, who may or may not be a glib talker (as so many of the Babas and Mas are=\r\n these days), but who has the necessary might and power to affect or initia=\r\nte changes in this land which would be of an irrevocable nature.&nbsp; It i=\r\ns time for a 1000 years of history to change. And only a soul of Ramakrishn=\r\na or Ma Sarada&#39;s caliber can do it. Anyone lesser, would only fizz out&nbsp=\r\n;with time.&lt;/P&gt;\n&lt;P&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/P&gt;\n&lt;P&gt;Not that&nbsp;they (Ramakrishna or Ma Sara=\r\nda or&nbsp;Swamiji) will find the work to be easy at all. For startes, the =\r\ndunces would be in confederacy against them. When Vivekanada, before he bec=\r\name world famous, had gone to Kasi, he was bitterly opposed by the &#39;scholar=\r\nly&#39; pandits of the city on various issues. Then a young not-yet-famous Vive=\r\nkananda got angry and decided he will leave Kasi and never return to that c=\r\nity untill he &quot;falls on society like a thunderbolt&quot;. Well, that is precisel=\r\ny what he did. He fell on Indian society like a thunderbolt, after which th=\r\nose very pandits of Kasi wrote to him, asking him to come and grace their c=\r\nity! &lt;/P&gt;\n&lt;P&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/P&gt;\n&lt;P&gt;So let us keep our fingers crossed and not&nbsp;=\r\nfocus on emtpy speculations, rather wait for the most interesting coming&nb=\r\nsp;decade to unfold in all its&nbsp;sound and fury.&lt;/P&gt;\n&lt;P&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/P&gt;\n&lt;P&gt;-R=\r\negards&lt;/P&gt;\n&lt;P&gt;&nbsp;Rajarshi&lt;/P&gt;\n&lt;P&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/P&gt;\n&lt;P&gt;&lt;FONT face=3DTahoma size=\r\n=3D2&gt;\n&lt;HR SIZE=3D1&gt;\n&lt;B&gt;&lt;SPAN style=3D&quot;FONT-WEIGHT: bold&quot;&gt;From:&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/B&gt; N=\r\narasimha PVR Rao &lt;pvr@...&gt;&lt;BR&gt;&lt;B&gt;&lt;SPAN style=3D&quot;FONT-WEIGHT: =\r\nbold&quot;&gt;To:&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/B&gt; vedic-astrology@yahoogroups.com; JyotishGroup@yahoogro=\r\nups.com; vedic-wisdom@yahoogroups.com&lt;BR&gt;&lt;B&gt;&lt;SPAN style=3D&quot;FONT-WEIGHT: bol=\r\nd&quot;&gt;Sent:&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/B&gt; Tue, 27 July, 2010 3:22:21 AM&lt;BR&gt;&lt;B&gt;&lt;SPAN style=3D&quot;FONT=\r\n-WEIGHT: bold&quot;&gt;Subject:&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/B&gt; [vedic-wisdom] On Rebirth (Re: Ram born =\r\nin Shishir by Prafulla)&lt;BR&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;BR&gt;&lt;SPAN style=3D&quot;DISPLAY: none&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;=\r\n/SPAN&gt; \n&lt;DIV id=3Dygrp-text&gt;\n&lt;P&gt;Namaste Ranjan,&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;&gt; After you die, =\r\nwhat would be your name and religion and nationality&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Name can change=\r\n on rebirth. Though religion usually stays the same, it CAN change. Nationa=\r\nlity can of course change too. Job, skills, external nature, looks, gender,=\r\n even yoni (human, cow, goat, chicken, tiger etc) can all change from birth=\r\n to birth.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Basically, the seed of one&#39;s new birth is formed at the t=\r\nime of one&#39;s death. As one&#39;s connection is severed with the body, the last =\r\ndesires/thoughts/ponderings of the mind become the seed for the next life. =\r\nNature chooses for one a future course that allows one to pursue those desi=\r\nres, as much as allowed by one&#39;s previous karmas and debts.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;If one i=\r\ns able to not entertain ANY desire as one element after another evaporates =\r\nin one&#39;s existence, one becomes liberated. All the spiritual sadhana we do =\r\nis a dress rehearsal.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;* * *&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;&gt; when we see you again and do=\r\n you know how\n we&lt;BR&gt;&gt; shall recognize you, IF WE EVER MEET YOU?&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;=\r\nIf I and you like each other and your rebirth and my rebirth meet each othe=\r\nr, they will start off taking a liking to each other. If I and you dislike =\r\neach other and your rebirth and my rebirth meet each other, they will start=\r\n off disliking each other. This will happen without either being consciousl=\r\ny aware of who one was and who the other person was, in the last life.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;=\r\nBR&gt;Instead, if your question is how we can recognize that so and so person =\r\nis a rebirth of Swami Vivekananda, so and so person is a rebirth of Paramah=\r\namsa Yogananda etc, the answer is complex.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;The reborn person may not=\r\n look like the old person or do similar work or have much *external* simila=\r\nrity. So it is difficult to &quot;recognize&quot; one. After all, Rama advocated eka =\r\npatni vrata (one wife principle), while Krishna had thousands of wives. Ram=\r\na was a great warrior and killed Ravana in the biggest war of his times. Kr=\r\nishna\n was a key player in the biggest war of his time, but did not take a =\r\nweapon at all. The game can be diffent in each coming..&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;* * *&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR=\r\n&gt;When it comes to recognizing the rebirth of a great soul, it can become a =\r\ntrap.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Ramakrishna explicitly told Sarada Mata that he would be back =\r\nafter 100 years and that everybody else who came with him would have to com=\r\ne back with him. When Sarada Mata and Lakshmi Devi protested, he said they =\r\ndid not have a choice! Even Swami Vivekananda said once in USA, &quot;I have to =\r\ncome back once more. The Master said I am to come back once more with him&quot;.=\r\n When questioned &quot;you have to come back because Shri Ramakrishna says so&quot;, =\r\nhe replied, &quot;souls like that have great power, Madam&quot;. On another occasion,=\r\n Ramakrishna said that people would get liberated en masse during his next =\r\ncoming and that would be the last opportunity for a long time to come.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;=\r\nBR&gt;Interestingly, two good saints claimed to be re-incarnations of\n Ramakri=\r\nshna since then. One of them is wrong (or perhaps both!). Another good sain=\r\nt suggested that she is the re-incarnation of Sarada Mata. Satya Sai Baba s=\r\naid that he identified a particular young man as the reincarnation of Swami=\r\n Vivekananda. Ramakrishna was surrounded by Sarada Mata and more than twent=\r\ny disciples of a very high caliber and different aptitudes. Together, they =\r\nnearly moulded the direction of spiritual India for the next century. None =\r\nof the claimants of rebirthhood are surrounded by people of such caliber or=\r\n fit the bill.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Thus, there can be false claimants to the rebirthhood=\r\n of a great soul! It is not that they are lying. They may simply be deludin=\r\ng themselves and of course ego is the root of delusion!&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;In fact, is =\r\nit necessary to recognize whether X is a rebirth of Y, given that X and Y a=\r\nre different and play a different game? A small discussion on this point vi=\r\ns-a-vis Ramakrishna Paramahamsa&#39;s example can be found\n in:&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;&lt;A href=\r\n=3D&quot;http://groups.yahoo.com/group/vedic-wisdom/message/807&quot; target=3D_blank=\r\n rel=3Dnofollow&gt;http://groups.yahoo.com/group/vedic-wisdom/message/807&lt;/A&gt;&lt;=\r\nBR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;* * *&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Though external factors like nationality, religion, nam=\r\ne, job, looks, gender etc can change, some internal factors may remain the =\r\nsame. Moreover, who one likes, who one dislikes, what values one is attract=\r\ned to internally, etc, may remain essentially the same.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;For example,=\r\n suppose rajput king Prithviraj was reborn as Muslim emperor Akbar (as said=\r\n by Vimalananda). One was a Hindu and the other was a Muslim. However, both=\r\n were very brave, unafraid of death, inherently spiritual, had a refined ta=\r\nste in fine arts and had deep conviction. The previous connections with raj=\r\nputs resulted in Akbar being born and raised when his mother was hiding at =\r\na rajput household, before moving to Delhi. Despite being a Muslim, he actu=\r\nally helped the Hindu causes (to the extent possible at\n that time) by putt=\r\ning an end to barbaric practices like killing defeated Hindu kings and all =\r\nHindu priests in conquered places. He promoted acceptance of other faiths, =\r\ncanceled pilgrimage taxes on Hindus and even came up with his own religion =\r\nof humanity towards the end of his life by integrating various religions. I=\r\nn one life, he tried to save India from invading barbarians. In another, he=\r\n was born as a cultured man amid barbarians and tried to save India by chan=\r\nging the ways of his own people. There is a subtle continuity in the agenda=\r\n at a deeper level!&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Best regards,&lt;BR&gt;Narasimha&lt;BR&gt;------------------=\r\n----------------------------------------&lt;BR&gt;Free Jyotish Software, Free Jyo=\r\ntish Lessons, Jyotish Writings,&lt;BR&gt;&quot;Do It Yourself&quot; ritual manuals for shor=\r\nt Homam and Pitri Tarpana:&lt;BR&gt;&lt;A href=3D&quot;http://www.vedicastrologer.org/&quot; t=\r\narget=3D_blank rel=3Dnofollow&gt;http://www.VedicAstrologer.org&lt;/A&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Films t=\r\nhat make a difference: &lt;A\n href=3D&quot;http://saraswatifilms.org/&quot; target=3D_bl=\r\nank rel=3Dnofollow&gt;http://SaraswatiFilms.org&lt;/A&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Spirituality: &lt;A href=\r\n=3D&quot;http://groups.yahoo.com/group/vedic-wisdom&quot; target=3D_blank rel=3Dnofol=\r\nlow&gt;http://groups.yahoo.com/group/vedic-wisdom&lt;/A&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Jyotish writings: &lt;A =\r\nhref=3D&quot;http://groups.yahoo.com/group/JyotishWritings&quot; target=3D_blank rel=\r\n=3Dnofollow&gt;http://groups.yahoo.com/group/JyotishWritings&lt;/A&gt;&lt;BR&gt;----------=\r\n------------------------------------------------&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;--- In &lt;A href=3D&quot;m=\r\nailto:JyotishGroup%40yahoogroups.com&quot; target=3D_blank rel=3Dnofollow ymailt=\r\no=3D&quot;mailto:JyotishGroup%40yahoogroups.com&quot;&gt;JyotishGroup@yahoogroups.com&lt;/A=\r\n&gt;, &quot;rohinicrystal&quot; &lt;jyotish_vani@...&gt; wrote:&lt;BR&gt;&gt;&lt;BR&gt;&gt; Dear Lok=\r\nesh_ji,&lt;BR&gt;&gt; &lt;BR&gt;&gt; As nearly ALL of do except this &quot;BABAJI&quot; Character=\r\n described in Lahiri Mahashay (no connection with the ayanamshaa that is ca=\r\nusing lot of problems for many!), Yukteshwar and Yognanda and Kriya Yoga --=\r\n shall probably die and hopefully be born again\n -- here is a simple questi=\r\non from a simpleton:&lt;BR&gt;&gt; &lt;BR&gt;&gt; After you die, what would be your nam=\r\ne and religion and nationality, when we see you again and do you know how w=\r\ne shall recognize you, IF WE EVER MEET YOU?&lt;BR&gt;&gt; &lt;BR&gt;&gt; I am not being=\r\n FLIPPANT at all but just reminding you and myself how evanescent each of u=\r\ns truly ARE!&lt;BR&gt;&gt; &lt;BR&gt;&gt; Rohiniranjan&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;\n&lt;STYLE type=3D=\r\ntext/css&gt;\n&lt;!--\n#ygrp-mkp {\nborder:1px solid #d8d8d8;font-family:Arial;margi=\r\nn:10px 0;padding:0 10px;}\n\n#ygrp-mkp hr {\nborder:1px solid #d8d8d8;}\n\n#ygrp=\r\n-mkp #hd {\ncolor:#628c2a;font-size:85%;font-weight:700;line-height:122%;mar=\r\ngin:10px 0;}\n\n#ygrp-mkp #ads {\nmargin-bottom:10px;}\n\n#ygrp-mkp .ad {\npaddin=\r\ng:0 0;}\n\n#ygrp-mkp .ad a {\ncolor:#0000ff;text-decoration:none;}\n#ygrp-spons=\r\nor #ygrp-lc {\nfont-family:Arial;}\n\n#ygrp-sponsor #ygrp-lc #hd {\nmargin:10px=\r\n 0px;font-weight:700;font-size:78%;line-height:122%;}\n\n#ygrp-sponsor #ygrp-=\r\nlc .ad {\nmargin-bottom:10px;padding:0 0;}\n\na {\ncolor:#1e66ae;}\n\n#actions {\n=\r\nfont-family:Verdana;font-size:11px;padding:10px 0;}\n\n#activity {\nbackground=\r\n-color:#e0ecee;float:left;font-family:Verdana;font-size:10px;padding:10px;}=\r\n\n\n#activity span {\nfont-weight:700;}\n\n#activity span:first-child {\ntext-tra=\r\nnsform:uppercase;}\n\n#activity span a {\ncolor:#5085b6;text-decoration:none;}=\r\n\n\n#activity span span {\ncolor:#ff7900;}\n\n#activity span .underline {\ntext-d=\r\necoration:underline;}\n\n.attach {\nclear:both;display:table;font-family:Arial=\r\n;font-size:12px;padding:10px 0;width:400px;}\n\n.attach div a {\ntext-decorati=\r\non:none;}\n\n.attach img {\nborder:none;padding-right:5px;}\n\n.attach label {\nd=\r\nisplay:block;margin-bottom:5px;}\n\n.attach label a {\ntext-decoration:none;}\n=\r\n